14,http://www.armslist.com/posts/2818014,"For Sale:  Stevens 410 ""Rare"" from 1939 -1945 very good condition for it age","Lansing Michigan, area, Lansing, Michigan",$ 125,"Listed On: Sunday, March 16, 2014",Shotguns,Savage Arms                                                                                ,410                                                                                ,Bolt Action                                                                                ,Shotgun,"I have a Savage Arms Company / Stevens Bolt Action 410, Model 58B. The blueing is really good for the age (we think from the 50's). wood in good no cracks, chips or splits, there are some very small scratches, bore is bright and shiny, bolt action is tight / not sloppy or wobbly , the 1 magazine looks very good with little to no wear, it appears that this gun has been fired much. I can sent more pictures. This was my wife's ""Great Grannies Gun"" passed down, to her dad, and then her, its been in a safe for the last 15 to 20 years only taken out to clean and oil. I bought a box of shells for it about 8 to 10 years ago thinking our youngest would shoot it, but he went from his 22 to his mom's semi auto 20g a. instead. The I shells bought will go with the gun.

I have lots of pictures that I can send. When I say its a rare gun, I have not found 1 of these on this site, or bunbrokes.com, gunsameraica.com......... or in any of the books I have that for gun information. This is what is stamped on the barrel:"" Savage Arms Corporation, Stevens Chioopee Falls, Mass. USA - MODEL 58B, 410 Bore Proof Tested 2 1/2"" and 3"" Shells""
